    body:
      'Iter 177. First real code-change iter since iter 172. Hardens lib/taostats.js getTaoPrice with a third fallback layer so cold-start Vercel lambdas survive a Taostats /api/price/latest/v1 429/5xx without throwing buildReport into http:500. ROOT CAUSE: iter 146 added a 60s-fresh + 5min-stale-OK in-memory priceCache to the getTaoPrice function, which serves stale on Taostats failure as long as priceCache.value is non-null. BUT: priceCache is in-memory (module-scope) and a cold-start lambda has priceCache.value===null, so the stale-OK branch can\'t engage; the catch block falls through to a bare throw. report.js buildReport line 2360 calls `const taoPrice = await getTaoPrice();` with NO try/catch around it (sequential Phase B before any of the section computations), so a single Taostats /price 429 on a cold instance fails the entire buildReport early — exactly the http:500 / wall_ms 6–17s pattern iter 173 + iter 176 sweep recorded on root, mum_root, mum_mantat. wall_ms 6–17s rules out the 60s pnlGroundTruth timeout; this is buildReport itself throwing during phase B, not pnlGroundTruth. PATCH: lib/taostats.js getTaoPrice catch block. After the existing stale-OK fallback fails (priceCache.value===null on cold start), attempts CoinGecko /api/v3/simple/price?ids=bittensor&vs_currencies=usd with a 4s AbortController timeout. On success, warms priceCache (so subsequent calls in the same lambda hit the fresh cache) and returns the CoinGecko price with a console.warn. On CoinGecko failure too, throws the original Taostats error (preserves error-path observability). The fallback is ONLY engaged on the cold-start cache-empty path, so warm hot-path latency is unchanged — every call where Taostats responds in <60s or where priceCache still holds a value <5min stale takes the original code path with zero overhead. Why CoinGecko: proven reachable from Vercel (lessons_vercel_binance_block.md explicitly calls out Binance as the blocked host and CoinGecko as the working alternative; the lesson was written for the binance/aud bug at /api/now-iso, the same conclusion applies here). Why 4s timeout: CoinGecko free tier is anon-rate-limited but typically responds in 100–300ms from Vercel; 4s is a generous ceiling that bounds the total getTaoPrice latency to Taostats_timeout (10s for /price per RPC_TIMEOUT) + 4s CoinGecko = 14s worst case, still well below the 60s function ceiling. Why fetch + AbortController not retry/backoff: this is a fallback hot path, not a primary; one shot, fail fast, surface the throw so an external monitoring layer can act on it. SMOKE EVIDENCE (/tmp/iter177_smoke.mjs run from VPS 2026-06-17T06:04Z): case A: Taostats key present, /api/price/latest/v1 → timeout 10000ms (VPS egress flap), CoinGecko fallback fired, returned $258.32, cache warmed at fetchedAt 1781676287097. Case B: Taostats key replaced with garbage_force_401, /api/price/latest/v1 → 401 immediately, CoinGecko fallback fired, returned $258.32, cache warmed. Both cases exercise the new catch-then-CoinGecko branch; the returned price ($258.32) is consistent with current TAO/USD market levels, proving the CoinGecko response shape parses correctly (j.bittensor.usd). DIFF: lib/taostats.js +30/-1 (new getTaoPriceCoinGecko helper + extended getTaoPrice catch block), lib/changelog-entries.js +8 (this entry). Bundle delta: ~1.1KB lib/taostats.js, no new dependencies (fetch + AbortController are Node ≥18 globals; Vercel runs Node 20). Pre-commit: `node --check lib/taostats.js` PASSED, `node --check lib/changelog-entries.js` PASSED. Tag: research (14th consecutive after 163/164/165/167/168/169/170/171/172/173/174/175/176; 166 was correctness interlude). NOT touched: lib/freeRpc.js, lib/freePnl.js, lib/report.js — the report.js call site at line 2360 stays as-is because the fallback is now baked into getTaoPrice itself, so every consumer benefits with zero call-site changes. EXPECTED VERIFY OUTCOME: re-running iter 176\'s 7-coldkey sweep should land at least one of root/mum_root/mum_mantat at http:200 + shadow_ok=true (instead of http:500), because the failure mode that took them down (Taostats /price flap on cold start) now routes through CoinGecko. The 2 wallets (subnets, mantat) that hit http:504 from function-load timeouts should also benefit: removing the Taostats /price cold-start failure mode means buildReport progresses past phase B even when Taostats is degraded, shaving the largest latency contributor on a Vercel-egress-throttled cold path. Iter 178 plan: re-run the 7-coldkey sweep, expect ≥5/7 http:200 with shadow_ok=true. If iter 178 confirms the fleet is clean, iter 179 = graduate shadow→primary (priority #1 milestone): when Taostats pnlGroundTruth surfaces available=false but shadowFreeApi.ok=true, the report surfaces shadow as the primary number with a footnote tag "free-API" and the Taostats-derived number as the fallback. ALTERNATE iter 178 if Taostats /api/account/history/v1 or /api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 remain the bottleneck (not just /price): chain the same cold-start-fallback pattern onto getHoldings + getBalanceHistory using the freeRpc getColdkeyStakeTao path (already exists per iter 169) — but only after iter 178 evidence pinpoints which call site is failing now. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~20 days, 1 comment).',
