    body:
      'Iter 165. Stake-leg implementation continues the load-bearing priority #1 free-API PnL arc that started with iter 163\'s research spike and iter 164\'s free-balance reader. Discovery this fire: the runtime API name was WRONG in the iter 163 spike doc — it said `SubtensorRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey` but VPS enumeration of finney\'s exported methods returned `Client error: Exported method SubtensorRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey is not found`. Probed 3 alternative pallet namespaces and discovered the correct one is `StakeInfoRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey` (returned 2556 hex chars / 1278 bytes of decodable SCALE data, 879ms round-trip on first probe). SCALE struct shape determined empirically by walking the bytes for Mantat: every entry shares the same hotkey 5876320…e403 (Mantat\'s sole delegated validator), suggesting struct layout `hotkey: AccountId32 + coldkey: AccountId32 + netuid: Compact<u16> + stake: Compact<u128> + locked: Compact<u128> + emission: Compact<u128> + drain: Compact<u128> + alpha_emission: Compact<u128> + is_registered: bool`. Per-entry size varies 75-81 bytes depending on Compact encoding of the six numeric fields. New export getColdkeyStakeAlpha(coldkey, opts) → { coldkey, entries, entryCount, totalStakeAlpha, latencyMs, source:"finney-rpc:StakeInfoRuntimeApi", note } where entries[] is [{hotkey, coldkey, netuid, stakeAlphaAtoms, stakeAlpha, lockedAlpha, emissionAlpha, alphaEmissionAlpha, isRegistered}]. decodeStakeInfo(hex) helper exported via __internals for test access. VPS validation: Mantat (5CTRC3sQ…ArLn) decoded 16 entries in 748ms, netuid=0 (Bittensor root, 1:1 alpha↔TAO) stake=2.403351α vs canonical from /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json `portfolio.wallets.mantat.positions[0]` alpha_shares=2.402892534 (drift 0.000459α = live chain emission since snapshot was taken). 12/12 canonical Mantat subnets recognized in the decoded set (0, 3, 4, 8, 9, 44, 51, 56, 64, 68, 95, 120); 4 additional netuids decoded (5, 14, 28, 75) likely represent small alpha holdings accumulated AFTER the snapshot was generated. LIMITATION: this reader returns RAW ALPHA-SHARE ATOMS per (hotkey, netuid). Canonical Mantat total_tao=12.2766τ is not directly comparable to a naive sum of decoded alpha amounts (280.374α this fire) because each subnet has a different alpha→TAO rate (root 1:1, but e.g. Chutes netuid=64 alpha=20.595 → TAO=1.347 = 0.0654 rate). Converting requires per-subnet pool reserves (TaoIn/AlphaIn from SubtensorModule storage), which is iter 166 scope. Stayed feature-flagged off (no lib/report.js import, no lib/taostats.js change). iter 166 will add getSubnetPrices() reading SubtensorModule::TaoIn(netuid)/AlphaIn(netuid) for each decoded netuid, compute rate=TaoIn/AlphaIn, expose total_stake_tao that should sum to within 0.5% of canonical 12.28τ. iter 167 = wire getColdkeyStakeAlpha + getSubnetPrices + getFreeBalance into a unified getColdkeyBalance(coldkey) gated behind FREE_PNL=1 env flag for shadow-mode validation. Pre-commit smoke: `node --check lib/freeRpc.js` PASSED. Zero production code path touched. Bundle delta: 0 bytes (uses existing @polkadot/util-crypto + @polkadot/util that iter 164 added; iter 165 adds compactFromU8a + hexToU8a imports from already-installed @polkadot/util). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
