    title: 'lib/freeRpc.js ships the first production-shippable free balance reader — getFreeBalance(coldkey) builds the System::Account storage key inline (twox_128("System") + twox_128("Account") + blake2_128_concat(public_key)) via @polkadot/util-crypto primitives, POSTs state_getStorage over plain HTTPS to entrypoint-finney.opentensor.ai (no WSS connect penalty), and manually SCALE-decodes the 56-byte AccountInfo to return free + reserved RAO/TAO with latency — VPS probe confirmed 0.7s round-trip per coldkey and balance match against iter 163 spike (Subnets free=0.500642τ, Mantat 0.296003τ) with zero API key and only ~3MB of bundled crypto dep weight added (vs @polkadot/api full bundle at ~80MB) — feature-flagged off (no lib/report.js import yet, iter 165 will add the stake leg via state_call SubtensorRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey before any production wire-in)',
    body:
      'Iter 164. Implements the iter 163 research-spike\'s recommended next iter: production-shippable free balance reader, HTTPS POST (not WSS) to avoid the 2.2s WS connect penalty on Vercel cold invokes, minimal @polkadot/util-crypto dep (~3MB installed, ~10kB needed at runtime for twox_128 + blake2_128_concat + ss58 decode) instead of full @polkadot/api (~80MB), manual SCALE decode of the AccountInfo bytes instead of metadata-driven type registry. Ship: new lib/freeRpc.js (97 lines) exports getFreeBalance(coldkey, opts) → { freeTao, reservedTao, freeRao, reservedRao, rawBytes, latencyMs, source:"finney-rpc", endpoint } and getFreeBalances(coldkeys, opts) for serial batching with per-coldkey error capture. Storage key construction: accountStorageKey() decodes SS58 to public key (32 bytes), computes twox_128("System") || twox_128("Account") || blake2_128(public_key) || public_key (concat), hex-encodes. RPC transport: AbortController with 10s default timeout, JSON-RPC 2.0 POST to https://entrypoint-finney.opentensor.ai, json.error propagated as Error. SCALE decode: VPS probe this fire returned 56-byte AccountInfo for active Bittensor coldkeys with layout `nonce u32 + consumers u32 + providers u32 + sufficients u32 (16 bytes header) + free u64 LE (8) + reserved u64 LE (8) + misc_frozen u64 (8) + fee_frozen u64 (8) + flags u64 (8)` — verified by Buffer.readBigUInt64LE(16) on Subnets giving 500642696 RAO = 0.500642τ (matches iter 163 spike\'s 0.500τ) and Mantat 296003889 RAO = 0.296003τ (matches iter 163\'s 0.296τ). Decoder ignores bytes 32-56 (frozen/flags variants) since we only need free + reserved for the PnL leg; null/empty result handled as zero balance for inactive coldkeys. Why HTTPS not WSS: Vercel serverless cold invokes pay the 2.2s WebSocket handshake on every fire (would be 4-15% of the 60s budget); plain HTTPS POST round-trips in 0.7s with no persistent connection — measured this fire on VPS, expect similar from Vercel egress modulo their TLS warm-up. Why @polkadot/util-crypto over hand-rolled crypto: xxhash-128 + blake2-128 + ss58 decode are non-trivial to hand-roll correctly (SS58 has a ss58Format prefix + checksum that depends on the network ID); @polkadot/util-crypto\'s API surface for these three primitives is tiny, well-tested, tree-shakeable. Bundle delta: package.json gains `@polkadot/util` and `@polkadot/util-crypto` at 14.0.3 (pinned to match the VPS probe install). Why feature-flagged off: iter 163\'s spike identified the stake leg as the LOAD-BEARING follow-on — free balance is only 3-9% of canonical total_tao for Jai\'s 7 pinned coldkeys (the bulk lives in SubtensorModule::Stake / alpha-share storage). Shipping a balance reader that ignores 90%+ of the wallet would be a regression vs Taostats /api/account/latest/v1, so freeRpc.js stays off until iter 165 lands the stake leg via state_call SubtensorRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey + SCALE decode (or per-subnet metagraph aggregation). Once both legs land, iter 166 = mirror of taostats.js getLatestBalance() ONLY (no history, no transfers) wired as a fallback path when Taostats /api/account/latest/v1 throws 429; iter 167+ defer the harder historical-series and transfers replacement to dedicated iters because both require archive-node block walks and extrinsic parsing far beyond the System::Account current-state read. Pre-commit smoke: `node --check lib/freeRpc.js` PASSED. No production code path touched (lib/report.js unchanged, lib/taostats.js unchanged); the 7-of-7 verify tally has zero risk surface from this iter. Discovery during VPS probe: when wake-prompt template tail "Root 5Cnz1juP…SLbinH" was used directly, @polkadot/util-crypto threw "Invalid decoded address checksum" — same hygiene gotcha iter 163 flagged. Probe script was restricted to Subnets + Mantat (canonical from /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json) to avoid the trap, per lessons_wake_prompt_coldkeys_unsafe.md. Smoke target after deploy: confirm the new dep landed in node_modules during Vercel build (build log will show @polkadot/util-crypto resolution); confirm changelog top H2 starts with "lib/freeRpc.js ships the first production-shippable free balance reader"; regression smoke on Subnets coldkey (should still verdict=matched since freeRpc.js is unused — pure additive iter, the 6 unchanged wallets carry zero risk). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
