    body:
      'Iter 163. Pivot away from iter 142 verify tally maintenance (now 7-of-7 ✓ after iter 162) toward load-bearing priority #1 from /home/Jai/.claude/projects/-home-Jai/memory/project_tao_wallet_report_priorities.md: replace the paid Taostats Standard plan with a free source for ground-truth PnL. Research-first per Jai\'s iter-47 redirect — VERIFY equivalence before swapping anything. Endpoint survey: probed four public Subtensor RPC hostnames from VPS with `system_chain` JSON-RPC POST. Results: entrypoint-finney.opentensor.ai 200/0.72s, archive.chain.opentensor.ai 200/0.64s, test.finney.opentensor.ai 200/0.67s, lite.sub.latent.to 200/0.81s. Note: bare finney.opentensor.ai does NOT resolve from the VPS — historical references to that hostname are stale, use entrypoint-finney. Balance probe: connected via @polkadot/api ^11.3.1 to wss://entrypoint-finney.opentensor.ai:443, queried system.account(AccountId32) for the four canonical coldkeys from iter 142 verify sweep. Results: Subnets 5EKFph3D…G5cd free=0.500642696τ reserved=0.093τ in 233ms, Mantat 5CTRC3sQ…ArLn free=0.296003889τ reserved=0.093τ in 233ms, Root 5Cnz1juP…binH free=0.003026419τ reserved=0 in 232ms, Mum_mantat 5HbWj5vb…jD1HL free=0.299916014τ reserved=0.093τ in 232ms. Connect was 2.2s one-time WS handshake; per-query 232ms; four serial queries 3.2s wall. WAKE-PROMPT COLDKEY HYGIENE: initial Root SS58 from the wake-prompt template was 5Cnz1juP…SLbinH (truncated wake-prompt tail) and @polkadot/api threw "Invalid decoded address checksum" — verified against /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json portfolio.root.coldkey canonical 5Cnz1juP8ZovhWkujaaHFZ1rJw2nyUsKf8s8543PbkSLbinH and re-ran (lessons_wake_prompt_coldkeys_unsafe.md invoked as designed). Findings: (1) free RPC reachable, fast, anonymous — 232ms beats Taostats Standard /api/account/latest/v1 latency (500-2000ms), no throttling on serial queries; (2) @polkadot/api handles SS58 decode, storage key construction (twox_128("System") + twox_128("Account") + blake2_128_concat), and AccountInfo Vec decode without manual SCALE work; (3) multiple redundant endpoints exist (4 verified) for trivial failover; (4) reserved 0.093τ on three of four wallets is the chain-staking reservation pattern. What this does NOT prove: (A) Stake leg — free balance was 0.003-0.5τ across the four wallets while canonical totals from snapshot.json are 5.4697τ (Subnets), 12.2836τ (Mantat), 9.118τ (Root), 1.5973τ (Mum_mantat). The bulk lives in SubtensorModule::Stake(hotkey, coldkey) or as alpha-shares per subnet. To replicate Taostats `/api/account/latest/v1` total_tao we\'d need a runtime API call (SubtensorRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey via state_call + SCALE decode) or N-subnet metagraph aggregation. (B) Historical balance series — Taostats `/api/account/history/v1` returns one row per day going back to wallet creation. Free RPC only serves current chain state directly; historical requires state_getStorageAt(key, blockHash) + a per-day block hash list (needs archive node + block-time math). (C) Transfers in/out — Taostats `/api/account/transfers/v1` is the only paid endpoint serving transfer events. Free equivalent requires parsing every block\'s extrinsics for the coldkey. Bundle-size + serverless feasibility: @polkadot/api install was 45s for ~80MB node_modules from VPS. WS connection per-request would add the 2.2s connect penalty per Vercel cold-invoke — risky against the existing 60s budget. Mitigations identified: use HTTP JSON-RPC instead of WSS (entrypoint-finney accepts plain HTTPS POST, no persistent connection, no connect penalty), and for the hot path build storage keys inline with `@polkadot/util-crypto` primitives (twox_128, blake2_128_concat — ~10kB) without the full @polkadot/api metadata bootstrap. Recommended next iters logged to lib/research/free-rpc-spike.md: iter 164 = HTTP POST + minimal storage-key construction for system.account, measure latency and bundle delta; iter 165 = stake leg via state_call SubtensorRuntimeApi_get_stake_info_for_coldkey decode path; iter 166 = if iter 164/165 land, write taoFreeRpc.js mirror of taostats.js getLatestBalance ONLY (no history, no transfers) wired as a fallback when Taostats /api/account/latest/v1 429s, measure verdict-landing rate uplift. Iters 167+ deferred (historical series + transfers via free RPC is much heavier — archive walks, extrinsic parsing). Code change for iter 163 is docs-only: lib/research/free-rpc-spike.md captures the probe results, endpoint survey table, decoding-path map, and the iter 164-166 plan so future fires can pick up without re-doing the spike. Why this is a legitimate iter: priority #1 has been parked since iter 47 redirect (~116 iters ago) while the 142-verify tally got rebuilt; with 7-of-7 stable, the next durable progress moves the free-API research forward not the polish backlog. Honest scope: no code path changed in lib/report.js or lib/taostats.js, no production behaviour change, no risk to the 7-of-7 verdict tally. Pure research-first artefact captured in the repo so the next iter can implement against documented findings rather than re-probing the same endpoints. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
