    body:
      'Iter 156. Direct unblock of the 2 remaining wallets still failing the iter 142 retroactive verify sweep, after iter 155 partially fixed the top-level Promise.all collider but exposed two distinct throttle endpoints as the actual root cause. Setup: iter 155 verify (2026-06-16T09:00:28Z) re-probed both wallets sequentially with 15s spacing. Mantat 5CTRC3sQ…ArLn returned http:500/17.3s with error "Taostats /api/delegation/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later." — UNCHANGED from iter 150 evidence, meaning the iter 155 top-level Phase B serialisation did NOT help Mantat because getDelegationHistory paginates internally within a sequential while-loop (already serialised), and Mantat at 12.28τ has many pages of delegation history. Each page-fetch consumes a throttle bucket; the default [1500, 3500] retry schedule gives only ~5s of retries per page, not enough to outwait the per-IP throttle reset between page-fetches. Mum_subnets 5GQAqusP…cw2V returned http:500/6.1s with error "Taostats /api/price/latest/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later." — NEW blocker, MOVED forward from iter 150\'s alpha_shares 429. Diagnosis: iter 155\'s Phase B puts getTaoPrice FIRST, so on cold-start Vercel instances (no warm 60s price cache), the price call hits the throttle bucket bare. Mantat\'s probe 15s earlier had just fired multiple delegation/v1 calls + the price call, depleting the bucket; Mum_subnets fired into a still-throttled bucket and 429\'d on price/latest/v1 immediately. Both failures fired the default [1500, 3500] retry schedule, exhausted budget, threw. The fix: extend TAOSTATS_PATH_RETRY_WAITS map to give both endpoints the [1500, 4000, 10000] schedule (~15.5s cumulative retries), mirroring iter 149\'s tax/v1 widening and iter 153\'s free-path widening — both proven patterns to outwait Vercel-egress per-IP throttle reset windows. Why pure retry widening and not also serialising getDelegationHistory pagination with inter-page delays: the Mantat blocker is per-page retry-budget exhaustion, not page-burst collision (the loop is already sequential, just no breathing room between pages). Widening the per-page retry schedule directly addresses the exhaustion; adding inter-page delays would compound by serialising MORE waits while still using the too-short retry schedule. Why pure retry widening for price/latest/v1 and not a CoinGecko fallback or pre-warming: the existing iter 146 server-side price cache (60s fresh, 5min stale-OK at lib/taostats.js:200-206) already serves stale-cached price on 429 for any warmed instance — only TRUE cold-starts with zero prior cache hit a hard 429. Wider retries give cold-starts ~15.5s to outwait the throttle window, after which the first successful fetch populates the cache and every subsequent call short-circuits — no CoinGecko coupling, no architectural creep. Trade-off honest: for Mum_mantat (verified at 56s in iter 154, near Vercel\'s 60s ceiling), the brittle-regression risk is REAL but BOUNDED. The price/latest/v1 widening only adds latency on cold-start instances with no warm cache (any prior successful fetch within the last 5min serves stale → zero retry budget consumed). The delegation/v1 widening only fires for wallets that paginate delegation history; Mum_mantat per iter 154 has lifetimeIn=0/lifetimeOut=0 = no delegation pages = no retry budget consumed by this widening. Worst case for any wallet: cold-start + price 429 fires full retry budget (~15.5s) + delegation 429 fires full retry budget (~15.5s) = ~31s of retry latency alone, which still fits Vercel\'s 60s maxDuration with ~25s headroom for actual work. Pre-commit smoke 12/12 PASS: 5 paths now in the override map (was 3), both new entries return [1500, 4000, 10000], iter 149 tax/v1 unchanged, iter 153 history/v1 + transfer/v1 unchanged, balance/dtao/yield endpoints still return default [1500, 3500], cumulative sums (15500 widened vs 5000 default), monotonic order on all wider schedules, iter 154 balanceFetchError thread unchanged, iter 155 Phase A/B split unchanged, price-cache state exports intact, retryWaitsFor accessor returns expected for unmapped paths. Post-deploy smoke target: re-probe Mantat 5CTRC3sQUTnPB6snh7LFAMCcWv6caMeFVmBhd78giH21ArLn + Mum_subnets 5GQAqusPNfe7qbtzXdpv6PcbgxQDG7K3nVwzmLPQKap5cw2V (canonical coldkeys verified against /home/Jai/bittensor-weekly/state/api_snapshot.json per lessons_wake_prompt_coldkeys_unsafe.md). IDEAL outcome: both http:200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and sheet-parity verdicts — 7-of-7 milestone complete (the entire iter 142 retroactive verify sweep done). ALTERNATE if Mantat still throws on /api/delegation/v1: the per-page retry-window assumption is wrong, pivot iter 157 to adding explicit inter-page delays inside getDelegationHistory (75ms mirror of iter 155 Phase B). ALTERNATE if Mum_subnets still throws on /api/price/latest/v1: Vercel\'s cold-start frequency is higher than assumed, pivot iter 157 to moving getTaoPrice into Phase A so it parallelises with screener/FX and doesn\'t serialise behind getHoldings/getDelegationHistory. ALTERNATE if Mum_mantat regresses into 60s timeout: the cold-start retry-budget worst case did fire, pivot iter 157 to capping a maxTotalRetryBudget across the buildReport stack. Non-regressive for the 5 already-verified wallets: TAOSTATS_PATH_RETRY_WAITS additions never fire on the happy path (no 429 = no retry), and the stale-OK price cache short-circuits the widening on warm instances. KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — same per-IP throttle endpoint coverage, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
