    body:
      'Iter 154. Symmetric correctness fix to iter 147 — that iter distinguished tax_fetch_failed from no_tax_data on the rows path, this iter does the same for the balance path. Setup: iter 152\'s re-sweep of Mum_mantat 5HbWj5vb…D1HL came back with a NEW reason value not seen before — `no_balance` with error:null and tax_fetch having SUCCEEDED (the tax/v1 throttle window had cleared by then). Investigation traced it to two parallel `.catch(() => null)` wrappers around getLatestBalance(coldkey): one at lib/report.js:189 inside pnlGroundTruth (non-prefetched path), one at lib/report.js:2283 at the upstream call site that pre-fetches balance for the main /api/report endpoint. Either path silently swallowed a /api/account/latest/v1 429 as a null balance, which the disposition logic in pnlGroundTruth then mapped to reason:"no_balance" — the exact same lying-shape iter 147 fixed for tax/v1. Mum_mantat is the dispositive case: tax_fetch_failed was NOT the blocker iter 152 fire (the tax/v1 throttle bucket happened to be open), the balance call was. Without this fix, every future fire where /tax/v1 happens to clear but /account/latest/v1 happens to 429 will produce the same lying "no_balance" verdict — and there\'s no way to distinguish from a genuinely empty wallet without inspecting Vercel runtime logs. Iter 154 ships the symmetric fix: (1) pnlGroundTruth signature gains a balanceFetchError parameter, mirroring the rowsFetchError parameter from iter 147; (2) the non-prefetched code path inside pnlGroundTruth replaces `.catch(() => null)` with a try/catch that captures the error message into a local balanceFetchError variable, mirroring the existing try/catch around getTaxReport at lib/report.js:183; (3) the disposition block at lib/report.js:192 adds a new reason value `balance_fetch_failed` (distinct from `no_balance`, which now only fires when the balance fetch genuinely SUCCEEDED but returned null/empty) before the no_balance branch, plus an optional error field naming the underlying exception string — mirroring the existing tax_fetch_failed reason; (4) the upstream call site at lib/report.js:2283 replaces its own `.catch(() => null)` with a closure that captures the error message into a `latestBalanceError` variable, then threads it through to pnlGroundTruth via the new balanceFetchError parameter — mirroring the existing fyRowsErrorBySy + trailingRowsError thread iter 147 set up for rows. Why both call sites need patching: the upstream prefetcher hands its pre-fetched balance to pnlGroundTruth via the balance: parameter — the conditional at lib/report.js:187 checks preFetchedBalance !== undefined (which null still satisfies) and uses it directly, bypassing the internal try/catch entirely. So a fix that only patched the internal path would still leak the lie through the prefetched call site. Both paths now capture the error via the new balanceFetchError plumbing and surface it as reason:"balance_fetch_failed". The UI consumers (Report.jsx, report-email.js, ai-insights.js, etc.) all gate downstream rendering on gt.available, so a new reason string is purely informational — same non-regressive shape iter 147 took. Pre-commit smoke target: re-probe Mum_mantat 5HbWj5vb…D1HL post-deploy. Three outcomes possible: (a) IDEAL EVIDENCE — http:200 with pnlGroundTruth.reason="balance_fetch_failed" and error string naming "/api/account/latest/v1 → 429" — proof iter 154 surfaces the actual blocker; (b) GENUINE EMPTY — reason still "no_balance" with no error — wallet is genuinely empty; (c) BONUS VERDICT — Vercel-egress balance throttle cleared in interim and Mum_mantat lands an iter 142 sheet-parity verdict (5th wallet to do so) via paid path. Trade-off: zero, like iter 147. Strictly more honest data shape — old behavior was "lie about why the verdict is missing", new behavior is "name the cause." Non-regressive: no existing consumer parses the reason field beyond the available boolean gate, so adding a new reason is invisible to all callers. The actual logic change is 6 lines (try/catch wrap + balanceFetchError variable + new disposition branch + closure on upstream + new parameter thread) — strictly additive shape that mirrors what iter 147 already did one level up the data chain. KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — diagnostic precision, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). Iter 155+ candidates: (a) once Mum_mantat\'s real blocker is surfaced, decide whether the right fix is to widen the /api/account/latest/v1 retry schedule (mirror iter 149\'s tax/v1 widening — pattern is identical), or to add the iter 146 server-side cache to balance fetches with a tight TTL since balances move every block (~12s); (b) serialise per-netuid alpha_shares fanout to unblock Mantat (delegation/v1 429) + Mum_subnets (alpha_shares 429) — the remaining 2 of Jai\'s 7 pinned coldkeys still blocked by the orthogonal fanout-burst problem; (c) the iter 153 wider free-path retry schedule is still UNTESTED in prod — Mum_root smoke fire saw paid /tax/v1 cleared so neither the iter 151 fallback nor the iter 153 wider free-path retries ever fired. PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
