      'Iter 149. Direct unblock of the queued retroactive iter 142 verify sweep that iter 147\'s correctness fix proved was being lied to. Setup: iter 147 changed pnlGroundTruth to distinguish reason:"tax_fetch_failed" from reason:"no_tax_data" — and the deploy-verify probe of Jai\'s Subnets coldkey 5EKFph3D8… came back showing tax_fetch_failed with error "Taostats /api/accounting/tax/v1 → 429: Rate Limited. Try Again Later." That confirmed the actual upstream cause was a 429 throttle on Vercel-egress, not a Taostats outage and not a structural "wallet has no tax data" condition. Iter 149 ships the fix: a per-endpoint retry-wait schedule keyed by Taostats path, alongside the existing iter 144 per-endpoint timeout map. The existing retry logic in taoGet already retries 429s, but its hardcoded [1500, 3500] waits only buy ~5s of cumulative backoff across 2 retries — short enough that the Taostats per-IP-range throttle window (apparently >5s for Vercel\'s shared egress range) hadn\'t reset by the time attempt 3 fired. The fix moves /api/accounting/tax/v1 to a wider [1500, 4000, 10000] schedule: 3 retries (vs 2), ~15.5s cumulative wait (vs 5s), doubling-ish pattern designed to outwait one full throttle reset window. Worst case math: 4 attempts × ~4s avg latency + 15.5s waits ≈ 31.5s, comfortably under the 25s per-attempt timeout × 4 ceiling (each attempt timeout fires independently) and well under Vercel\'s 60s maxDuration (iter 141). Other endpoints keep the default [1500, 3500] schedule — the iter 147 sweep also showed /api/delegation/v1 and /api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 429ing on 4 wallets, but those are a fanout-burst problem better fixed by sequence (iter 150 candidate: serialise the per-netuid alpha_shares fanout instead of parallel-fanning) rather than papering over with wider retries. The shape mirrors the existing TAOSTATS_PATH_TIMEOUTS map and timeoutFor() helper from iter 144 — TAOSTATS_PATH_RETRY_WAITS object + retryWaitsFor(path) helper + _getTaostatsRetryWaitsFor test-only accessor. Unknown paths fall through to TAOSTATS_DEFAULT_RETRY_WAITS, so the change is strictly additive — every existing endpoint that worked before still gets the same schedule, only /accounting/tax/v1 gets the wider one. Pre-commit smoke 12/12 PASS: default schedule for /price/latest matches old behavior, tax/v1 returns the new wider schedule, unknown path falls back to default, tax has 3 retries vs default 2, tax cumulative wait sum is 15500ms, schedule is monotonically increasing (so backoff genuinely widens each attempt), default cumulative is 5000ms unchanged, iter 144 timeout map is intact (tax 25s, price 10s), iter 146 price cache test-only exports are intact. Non-regressive: taoGet signature unchanged, all callers transparent to the per-path retry config. The visible behavior change is only on retry paths — happy-path GET on tax/v1 still returns in one fetch with no waits. Trade-off: a tax/v1 endpoint that 429s on all 4 attempts now wastes ~15.5s + 4 × actual-call-time (probably ~5s total on instant 429s, longer on slow 429s) before throwing tax_fetch_failed — but the previous behavior threw the same error 10s sooner with a verdict that lied. Iter 149 trades 10s of optimistic-but-wrong "fast fail" for a real chance at success; the verdict is the entire value of iter 142, so the trade lands clean. Smoke-verify plan post-deploy: re-run the iter 147 sanity probe on Subnets 5EKFph3D8… — expect either (a) IDEAL: 200 with pnlGroundTruth.available=true and a parity verdict (iter 142 sheet-parity finally lands on a non-Root wallet — the headline win), or (b) STILL BLOCKED but more thoroughly retried: 200 with pnlGroundTruth.reason="tax_fetch_failed" + error string with timestamp ~15s later than iter 147\'s — proof the retries genuinely fired before giving up. Both outcomes inform iter 150 routing: ideal → complete the remaining 5 of Jai\'s 7 pinned coldkeys verify sweep (Mantat, Mum_root, Mum_smf, Mum_subnets, Mum_mantat) spaced 13s apart, screenshot §0 9th parity row on each; still blocked → next step is either to wait for Taostats Pro plan upgrade (the throttle bucket may be ungetable around) or to add an alternate ground-truth path via free /api/account/history + /api/transfer reconstruction (FREE_PNL=1 mode in lib/taostats.js already supports this — iter 150 could promote it from opt-in to fallback-on-429). KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — calibration/reliability fix, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). PR #1 still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~19 days).',
