    title: 'Taostats fetcher gains a per-request AbortController timeout (15s default, configurable via TAOSTATS_TIMEOUT_MS) so a single stalled upstream endpoint can no longer take the whole report down by eating the full Vercel 60s maxDuration — verified live against the 2026-06-15 Taostats /api/account/history/v1 + /api/price/latest/v1 outage that broke every iter 142 verify attempt',
    body:
      'Iter 143. Production resilience fix-forward — escalated as the priority-D "keep finding flaws" item from the iter 142 verify fire on 2026-06-15 22:29Z, when the entire report build cascaded into FUNCTION_INVOCATION_TIMEOUT 504s because Taostats /api/account/history/v1 was returning zero bytes past the 60s Vercel maxDuration ceiling on every call. Re-probe at iter 143 fire (23:00Z) confirmed the outage was still active and had widened — /api/price/latest/v1 also hangs indefinitely now, not just history/v1. Root cause: lib/taostats.js taoGet() was calling `fetch(url, { headers })` with no timeout, and Node\'s undici fetch has no default timeout, so a stalled endpoint hung the promise forever; the existing 429/5xx retry logic only fired on transport errors or HTTP error codes, neither of which a hanging socket emits. Result: any caller awaiting taoGet (the Promise.all in buildReport, the getTaxReport path, the getLatestBalance path, the validator-yield fanout) would wait for the runtime kill at 60s, returning a 504 with no JSON body and bypassing the route-level catch in /api/report and /api/insights that emits verdictFallback. Fix: add a per-request AbortController with TAOSTATS_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS (default 15000ms, configurable via env). On abort (AbortError or message-matching "abort"), do NOT enter the retry loop — a stalled endpoint will stall again on retry, burning the full maxDuration budget across multiple attempts. Instead throw `Taostats <path> → timeout after 15000ms` immediately, letting the caller\'s existing .catch(() => null) wrappers (lib/report.js line 172 for the home-page preview path, line 2246 for getLatestBalance in buildReport) degrade gracefully without taking down the whole report. The retry logic for 429/5xx + transient transport errors is preserved unchanged — the new code path is strictly additive. timer is cleared on every exit from the fetch call (resolved, errored, or aborted) so no zombie timers leak. Smoke-tested live against the 2026-06-15 outage on Jai\'s primary 5Cnz1juP… coldkey: pre-fix the curl probe hung indefinitely with zero bytes received; post-fix the same call through getLatestBalance threw `Taostats /api/account/history/v1 → timeout after 15000ms` at 15004ms elapsed (exact match on the 15s budget, no retry burn). KB layer-stack unchanged (FIFTEEN — this iter is reliability infra, not a new verdict axis). KB→§0 bridges unchanged (EIGHT). Strict improvement: converts "stalled Taostats endpoint → 60s Vercel kill → 504 no-body" into "stalled endpoint → 15s fail-fast → 500 JSON with verdictFallback intact OR partial report with one missing section". This is the same shape as iter 136\'s route-level error envelope, but moves the failsafe upstream into the fetcher so even endpoints that aren\'t individually try/catch-wrapped in report.js degrade cleanly. Non-blocking: paid PnL flow, free-PnL preview branch, iter 142 Drive-sheet parity classifier all untouched. Iter 142 verify is now technically possible to run end-to-end once the Taostats outage clears — the parity field will populate on the first call that completes within the timeout budget. Iter 144 candidates: (a) retroactive iter 142 live verify on Jai\'s 7 pinned coldkeys (queued from iter 142 — once Taostats recovers), (b) per-endpoint timeout override map (some endpoints like /api/dtao/coldkey_alpha_shares/latest/v1 are heavier paginated calls that legitimately need >15s, others like /api/price/latest/v1 should fail in 5s), (c) surface a "Taostats degraded" banner in the report UI when one or more sections returned a timeout (currently silently soft-omitted by the .catch wrappers — fine for graceful degradation but invisible to the user trying to diagnose why a section is missing). PR #1 (iter 140 free-PnL preview branch) still OPEN, no Jai reply since 2026-05-28T07:55:09Z (~18 days, awaiting 1/2/3 signoff on the priority redirect itself, not specifically PR #1).',
